For a bias audit of an AEDT if an employer wants to use it to screen resumes and schedule interviews for a job posting in New York City, the calculations required at a minimum are: 
1) Calculate the selection rate for each category, including sex and race/ethnicity categories required to be reported to the EEOC, and compare the selection rates to the most selected category to determine an impact ratio; 
2) Calculate the median score for the full sample of applicants; 
3) Calculate the scoring rate for individuals in each category.
